docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump awarded the Medal of Freedom to the former N.B.A. great Jerry West on Thursday, the second time in two weeks that the president has honored a long-retired standout from a league whose current generation of stars is known for refusing to visit his White House.

docs.abstract: The Trump administration largely concedes that adult detainees experience grueling conditions in federal custody. But it also wants to appear sensitive to migrant children.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Vice President Mike Pence visited a pair of migrant detention centers on the southwestern border late last week, he witnessed several hundred men packed into a cage amid sweltering heat and a foul stench — a scene that provoked national outrage and that Mr. Pence conceded was “tough stuff.”

headline.main: Pence’s Border Trip Illustrates Conflicting Messages About Detained Migrants
headline.print_headline: ‘Tough Stuff’ Pence Saw at Migrant Centers Fuels Battle Over Blame
